WEBVTT

1
00:01:40.850 --> 00:01:44.690
It's spring, so I thought I could get away 
with no jacket for a smoke run,

2
00:01:44.690 --> 00:01:47.230
but it still gets 
pretty chilly at night, huh?

3
00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:51.320
I'll have a smoke somewhere 
before I go home.

4
00:01:54.200 --> 00:01:57.740
Yamada-chan, I'll take over.

5
00:01:57.740 --> 00:01:59.120
Cheers.

6
00:02:04.080 --> 00:02:06.500
He didn't show up tonight.

7
00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:09.670
Overtime? Is he stuck 
at work until morning?

8
00:02:09.670 --> 00:02:11.960
Oh, and one more thing.

9
00:02:11.960 --> 00:02:12.840
Yes?

10
00:02:13.220 --> 00:02:17.050
The manager wants to speak 
with you before you leave.

11
00:02:25.100 --> 00:02:26.350
Tayama-san, good ev—

12
00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:30.940
Yikes.

13
00:02:37.620 --> 00:02:39.410
Hey, if it ain't Sasaki-san.

14
00:02:39.410 --> 00:02:40.450
Hey.

15
00:02:40.450 --> 00:02:43.040
Don't just stand there. Come take a seat.

16
00:02:43.040 --> 00:02:44.040
Thanks.

17
00:02:49.500 --> 00:02:50.670
Tayama-san, did something—

18
00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:53.050
Were you off work today?

19
00:02:53.050 --> 00:02:53.510
Huh?

20
00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:56.090
Oh, yeah, for once.

21
00:02:57.800 --> 00:03:00.430
That response just screams sweatshop.

22
00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:09.360
Glad you got a day off.

23
00:03:28.420 --> 00:03:29.960
Aren't you gonna smoke?

24
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.290
It's cold out, so I'm getting a drink.

25
00:03:32.750 --> 00:03:34.420
Join me.

26
00:03:37.510 --> 00:03:39.260
When you're feeling down,

27
00:03:39.260 --> 00:03:43.970
a hot drink helps more than 
cigarettes and alcohol, you know?

28
00:03:50.350 --> 00:03:53.440
I got a complaint 
for the first time in ages.

29
00:03:53.690 --> 00:03:56.280
"I've always thought 
her customer service was flawless,

30
00:03:56.280 --> 00:03:59.280
but I smelled cigarette smoke 
on her today. I expected better."

31
00:03:59.780 --> 00:04:04.330
The boss told me not to take it to heart, 
'cuz it's just unreasonable whining.

32
00:04:10.790 --> 00:04:12.460
But when this crap happens,

33
00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:14.840
everything starts to feel so stupid.

34
00:04:20.880 --> 00:04:22.300
That's sad.

35
00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:28.980
I don't get feeling betrayed by somebody 
as soon as you see a new side to them.

36
00:04:29.850 --> 00:04:31.650
They're both the same person, you know?

37
00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:38.070
Oh, but I'm not one to talk.

38
00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:42.570
I don't even know what section you work.

39
00:04:46.290 --> 00:04:50.620
S-Sorry, I stepped out dressed 
too lightly, and I keep sneezing.

40
00:04:56.500 --> 00:04:58.880
Tayama-san? What are you doing?!

41
00:05:03.640 --> 00:05:04.890
You can borrow that for tonight.

42
00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:13.980
It's warm. Thank you, Tayama-san.

43
00:05:28.080 --> 00:05:29.370
No, thank you.

44
00:05:39.420 --> 00:05:42.470
Also, I'm sorry, but I have to say this.

45
00:05:43.090 --> 00:05:45.090
I don't drink coffee.

46
00:05:45.930 --> 00:05:48.430
You look surprised.

47
00:05:48.430 --> 00:05:50.560
That's not why.

48
00:05:51.060 --> 00:05:53.100
I actually don't drink it either.

49
00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:56.690
Let's just get another drink, huh?

50
00:05:56.690 --> 00:05:59.270
Big Bad Bull for me, then.

51
00:06:06.490 --> 00:06:08.830
Lovely weather today.

52
00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:12.790
Nothing feels better 
than the warm sunlight in spring.

53
00:06:13.330 --> 00:06:15.870
It warms the tired cockles 
of my heart and soul.

54
00:06:17.710 --> 00:06:21.340
Especially after a client chewed me out.

55
00:06:24.340 --> 00:06:26.840
I need to get back to work.

56
00:06:26.840 --> 00:06:30.350
Guess I'll buy some lunch 
at Super S on the way back.

57
00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:35.850
Tayama-san probably works 
the night shift, right?

58
00:06:38.610 --> 00:06:41.150
I doubt she'd be here right now...

59
00:06:45.990 --> 00:06:47.740
Tayama-san...

60
00:06:48.990 --> 00:06:49.990
What?!

61
00:06:49.990 --> 00:06:52.490
Y-Y-Yamada-san?!

62
00:06:52.490 --> 00:06:54.000
Hello!

63
00:06:54.290 --> 00:06:56.710
Wh-What are you doing here?

64
00:06:56.710 --> 00:07:00.000
Wait, you work during the day, too?

65
00:07:00.290 --> 00:07:02.920
Sasaki-san, calm down, will you?

66
00:07:02.920 --> 00:07:05.260
Oh, s-sorry about that.

67
00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:10.220
I mostly do night shifts, 
but I'm filling in for someone today.

68
00:07:10.220 --> 00:07:12.010
And I'm here because...

69
00:07:12.390 --> 00:07:14.270
Calm down... Calm down.

70
00:07:18.600 --> 00:07:21.150
It's the only spot here 
with a vending machine.

71
00:07:21.150 --> 00:07:23.400
Oh, is that so.

72
00:07:23.400 --> 00:07:25.530
Did you get off work early?

73
00:07:25.530 --> 00:07:29.030
No, I was on my way back,

74
00:07:29.030 --> 00:07:31.870
but if Tayama-san was here, 
I thought I could join her for a smoke.

75
00:07:31.870 --> 00:07:32.950
Urk!

76
00:07:32.950 --> 00:07:36.710
Sorry, Yamada-san, 
I know I shouldn't be here!

77
00:07:36.710 --> 00:07:40.130
I'm just taking advantage of 
Tayama-san's gracious offer!

78
00:07:40.130 --> 00:07:42.590
She didn't do anything wrong!

79
00:07:43.670 --> 00:07:45.420
So, uh...

80
00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:50.890
It's all right, Sasaki-san. 
I knew that already.

81
00:07:51.930 --> 00:07:54.350
Tayama-chan told me.

82
00:07:54.350 --> 00:07:57.060
Oh, she did?

83
00:07:57.310 --> 00:07:59.810
You two must be good friends.

84
00:08:02.560 --> 00:08:03.820
Sa-slow-ki.

85
00:08:04.690 --> 00:08:05.570
Huh?

86
00:08:05.570 --> 00:08:07.650
Yes, we're very close!

87
00:08:07.650 --> 00:08:09.070
I knew it.

88
00:08:09.360 --> 00:08:12.320
You must have a lot in common.

89
00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:17.830
You're both very attentive and thoughtful.

90
00:08:20.830 --> 00:08:23.670
Oh, right. Uh, Yamada-san?

91
00:08:23.670 --> 00:08:24.670
Yes?

92
00:08:24.670 --> 00:08:26.090
Uh...

93
00:08:26.800 --> 00:08:29.590
Is Tayama-san doing okay?

94
00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:33.600
She is, why?

95
00:08:34.050 --> 00:08:36.770
Is this about the complaint?

96
00:08:36.770 --> 00:08:43.360
Yeah. She told me a little about it.

97
00:08:43.770 --> 00:08:46.110
I was worried if she'd be okay.

98
00:08:48.110 --> 00:08:49.740
She's fine.

99
00:08:50.070 --> 00:08:53.370
I was worried, too, 
but you know what she said?

100
00:08:53.620 --> 00:08:56.450
That she forgot all about it after 
eating some ramen and going to sleep.

101
00:08:57.950 --> 00:09:00.620
Is that so? Glad to hear it.

102
00:09:01.080 --> 00:09:06.170
I hope you'll let her vent to you again.

103
00:09:06.170 --> 00:09:07.880
Oh, but...

104
00:09:08.210 --> 00:09:13.760
If she's already put it behind her, 
I don't think I should bring it up again.

105
00:09:14.640 --> 00:09:18.270
It doesn't have to be 
about this particular matter.

106
00:09:18.640 --> 00:09:23.190
I'll let her know that you were 
concerned about her.

107
00:09:23.770 --> 00:09:28.280
What? A-Are you sure? 
Wouldn't I be overstepping?

108
00:09:28.610 --> 00:09:32.030
Overstepping? When she was 
the one who came to you about it?

109
00:09:32.780 --> 00:09:34.280
It's a bit late for that now.

110
00:09:34.570 --> 00:09:38.160
Oh, true.

111
00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:41.910
By the way, Yamada-san.

112
00:09:42.290 --> 00:09:44.920
Thank you for the other day.

113
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:47.790
I heard from Tayama-san.

114
00:09:48.460 --> 00:09:52.920
She told me you were worried 
I seemed down in the dumps.

115
00:09:53.430 --> 00:09:59.100
I never got the chance to thank you, as 
I didn't want to bother you while working.

116
00:09:59.100 --> 00:10:00.560
Oh, that's fine.

117
00:10:03.560 --> 00:10:10.070
Work had me down, so I really appreciated 
having someone look out for me.

118
00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:18.080
I'm glad. As long as 
I wasn't overstepping...

119
00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:21.700
Wait, overstepping?

120
00:10:22.700 --> 00:10:25.210
I suppose it's a bit late for that, too.

121
00:10:27.250 --> 00:10:29.840
That would be the natural conclusion.

122
00:10:32.590 --> 00:10:35.970
Oh, I'm sorry for keeping you.

123
00:10:35.970 --> 00:10:37.090
Not at all.

124
00:10:37.390 --> 00:10:42.600
I've been wanting to speak with you like 
Tayama-chan, so I'm glad I got the chance.

125
00:10:44.640 --> 00:10:49.190
She's not here right now, 
but feel free to have a smoke.

126
00:10:49.190 --> 00:10:51.110
Thank you.

127
00:10:52.730 --> 00:10:56.110
Actually, I'll refrain today.

128
00:10:56.110 --> 00:10:58.870
I wouldn't want to get 
the smell of smoke on you.

129
00:11:00.030 --> 00:11:02.580
Sorry to take up your valuable break time.

130
00:11:03.250 --> 00:11:04.040
See you.

131
00:11:09.670 --> 00:11:10.840
Sasaki-san.

132
00:11:10.840 --> 00:11:11.800
Yes?

133
00:11:24.390 --> 00:11:27.810
You've had a petal 
in your hair this whole time.

134
00:11:29.270 --> 00:11:31.480
What? The whole time?

135
00:11:31.480 --> 00:11:32.440
Yeah.

136
00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:35.610
A geezer with a flower...

137
00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:37.900
It was so cute,

138
00:11:37.900 --> 00:11:39.780
I couldn't bring myself to tell you.

139
00:11:40.070 --> 00:11:41.320
Sorry about that.

140
00:11:42.780 --> 00:11:45.910
No, uh, thank you.

141
00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:55.670
I didn't expect that from Yamada-san.

142
00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:59.090
She's got a playful side, too, huh?

143
00:12:22.070 --> 00:12:24.700
Sasaki-san's so dense,

144
00:12:29.710 --> 00:12:30.960
it's almost funny.
